		<div class="md:col-span-3 space-y-6">
			<h1 class="font-serif text-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight">
				Clarity Workshop
			</h1>
			<p class="font-thin text-xl md:text-2xl leading-relaxed">
				A 1-week focused engagement that gives climate startup leaders the clarity they need to move forward with confidence in technical projects.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="md:col-span-2"></div>
	</section>

	<section class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-8 md:gap-12 py-12 md:py-16">
		<div class="md:col-span-3 space-y-6">
			<h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold font-serif text-heading tracking-tight">
				Your project is pulling you in too many directions
			</h2>

			<p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg text-body-subtle leading-relaxed">
				The list of open questions keeps growing with no clear priority.
			</p>

			<p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg text-body-subtle leading-relaxed">
				You know that you need to put technical solutions together but don't want to be dragged into a complex project with no clear benefits. You're not sure if you need something custom, or if you can do well with off-the-shelf software.
			</p>

			<p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg text-body-subtle leading-relaxed">
				Maybe you have an idea that feels promising but you aren't sure it's actually feasible or how to explain it to a developer. Maybe you have wireframes but no clear path from those designs to working software.
			</p>

			<p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg text-body-subtle leading-relaxed">
				Or maybe development is already underway and something has gone sideways: vendor relations, performance, scope creep.
			</p>

			<p class="font-thin text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
				Every week of uncertainty is a week of lost momentum. You keep hoping things will become clearer as you amass more info. They don't.
			</p>
		</div>

